A police officer was shot dead and robbed of his gun in an attack in Kayole area, Nairobi on Tuesday at dawn.  The officer, who is attached to Diplomatic Police Unit, was walking to catch a matatu when was ambushed by suspected thugs.  He was rushed to the Mama Lucy Hospital where he succumbed to injuries.  Police say the officer was going to work at about 6.30 am when the incident happened.  The gang grabbed a pistol from the officer and escaped on foot. No one has been arrested over the incident. Also read: Four suspected thugs shot dead in Kawangware, stolen motorbike recovered Click
